metadata for that process to function correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating potential issues**\\n\\nI’m noticing a potential issue where, without a CacheManager, the Cache.dispose might be using a null cacheManager when it's still alive. That could lead to problems, right? I think I need to inspect the dispose function more closely to understand if it’s functioning correctly despite the absence of a CacheManager. It seems like there might be some complexity here, so it’s worth taking a deeper look!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yvnx49601VrC6MwBXXekRojG|fc_0924c862dc9f80ab0169f552f817e4819faec843044cc4b59f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"void dispose\\(|public void dispose\" /home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/master/forge/local_repositories/source_context/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/main/extracted/net/sf/ehcache/Cache.java | head -20", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 598, "output": 1055, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28277, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777685221776, "responseId": "resp_0924c862dc9f80ab0169f552e644f4819f88f65909f5231ef5"}}
